f.d:
Those who have sustained the holy Dharma of the Tathāgatas
Have no faults for Māra to find;
They have no regrets, and in the same way, no worries.
They have no fetters, nor even minor distortions.}

{Those who have sustained the holy Dharma of the Tathāgatas—
The learned always take delight in them.
They are delightful to gods, titans, and humans;
They are praised as children of the Buddhas.}

We will give up wealth and prestige;
We will give up all praise;
We will not give up this Dharma,
Which shows the way to the pristine awareness of the Buddhas.

Even if a monk is immoral,
Stealing his saffron robe, or beating him,
Having him thrown in prison,
[67] Or forcing him to become a layman;
Doing any one of the five actions of immediate retribution;
Holding wrong views;
And causing division in a village
Are said by the Victor to be root downfalls.

Giving teachings on emptiness to people
Who have not trained their minds;
When people have set out towards Buddhahood,
Turning them back from full Awakening;
Joining the Great Way
After giving up on the Vows of Individual Liberation;
Believing that the Way of the Disciples
Does not enable people to give up attraction and the other poisons;

Because of grasping,
Advertising your own abilities to others;
For the sake of profit, fame, and prestige,
Disparaging others;
Or falsely saying,
“I am someone who accepts deep truths”;
Ordering religious wanderers to be punished;
Giving away the property
Of the Three Jewels;
Giving up resting meditation;
Giving items designated for retreat practitioners
To people who merely recite prayers;

Giving up the Awakening Mind;
Out of sharp greed and avarice,
Not giving things to people who ask for them;
Beating sentient beings out of rage;
While making an effort to please others,
Not being patient with sentient beings;
Due either to reactive emotions or to conformity with others,
Proclaiming an imitation of the holy Dharma.

This kind of intoxication is the root of all heedlessness;
You should never have contempt for monks who are less advanced than you are.
This religion works in gradual stages;
No one can attain Awakening in one single lifetime.[xxxvi]

About delighting in talking, the same text says:
He is intoxicated with his own learning and so lacks respect for others;
He is attracted to quarrelsome speech;
He is robbed of his mindfulness and lacks awareness.
These are the disadvantages of delighting in talking.

He is very far away from introspection;
He has no calmness in body or mind;
He goes through many cycles of elation and depression.
These are the disadvantages of delighting in talking.

His mind wavers and trembles like the grass;
He certainly has many doubts;
His mind never becomes stable.
These are the disadvantages of delighting in talking.

About delighting in sleep, the text says:
The net of delusion grows bigger around them;
They hold false views and have doubts;
They often act out of false views,
Because they don’t progress beyond pleasant snoozing.[xlv]

You don’t have a wife, sons, or daughters,
Friends or a group of relatives;
You have no male or female servants and no political power;
Once you are ordained, don’t quarrel!

Here “stable Awakening Mind” specifies an ordinary person who has attained mental strength, but it is not referring to those who have entered the Stages, because the same text says: “If you try to get your gifts back, try to profit by hinting [to donors about what you want], but wish to enter into the light from deep darkness, after you have fallen into error many times, you will get results.” This counteracts the timid mind that thinks, “How could I do even a little bit of good?” But it is impossible that someone who has entered the Stages, has gone completely beyond the lower realms, has great waves of energy and has gathered an immeasurable mass of goodness, could have this problem.
If, due to ignorance of the mantras, you recite additional syllables, there is no problem. If you recite it with some syllables left out, no problem. A defect in the ritual also won’t be a problem. But you should sustain the power of faith, the power of Awakening Mind, and the power of giving up everything, and without analyzing too much, just do it. {A bodhisattva who recites this will certainly, in this very life, achieve vision, and anything else she wants.}
Moreover, you should provide protection with this, the mantra of all vajra holders:

[153] The noble Rāṣṭrapāla Sūtra also says,
By the influence of pride, the deluded
Are born in the lower realms, without the opportunity to practice;
Are born in poverty, or in lowly families;
Are born blind, or weak,[xxxvii] with little stamina.[12]

The Sūtra on King Bhaiṣajyaguru of the Lapis Lazuli Radiance also says:
Those who keep five precepts, and those who keep ten precepts, and those who keep the four hundred precepts of the bodhisattva vow, and those monks who have gone forth from the home life and who keep two hundred fifty precepts, and those nuns who keep five hundred precepts, and all those who have deviated from whatever training vows and precepts they may have taken—if they are afraid of the terrors of the lower realms, they should remember the name of the Tathāgata King Bhaiṣajyaguru of the Lapis Lazuli Radiance, and make offerings to him according to their wealth.[xlviii] It may be expected that they will not go to the lower realms.
{And any woman who, at the time of giving birth, experiences severe, abnormal pains, if she quickly makes offerings to the Blessed One, the Tathāgata King Bhaiṣajyaguru of the Lapis Lazuli Radiance, she will be saved. And the child will be born with fully complete limbs, well featured, beautiful and appealing to look at, of sharp faculties, intelligent, free from illness, and unharmed. But this will not be achieved through mere words, without faith.}

The threefold world is changeable like an autumn cloud;
The birth and death of living beings is like a stage in a theatre.[xi]
Our time passes like lightning in the sky;
It goes quickly, lightly, swiftly, like a fast-running mountain stream.

They cause you to forget mindfulness and produce darkness;
They create reasons for fear and are always the root of suffering;
They cause the jungle of the craving for existence to grow.
Sensual pleasures are dangerous, associated with reactivity.

Why is this? For example, Your Majesty, suppose that a lion, the king of beasts, having physical beauty and speed, with well-grown claws and dreadful teeth,[xxv] went among a herd of deer, seized a deer, and did whatever he wanted with him, and that deer, having met with those powerful, ferocious jaws, was powerless. In the same way, Your Majesty, people who have been pierced by the impalement stake of death, having lost their intoxication,[xxvi] {with no guardian, with no refuge,} with no friend to help,
with their vitals pierced,[xxvii] with their joints leaking, with their flesh and blood drying up, tormented and thirsty, with their faces changing,[xxviii] with their hands and feet shaking, unable to do anything, powerless, their bodies smeared with saliva, mucus, urine, and feces,[xxix]
{with their faculties of sight, hearing, smell, taste, touch, and introspection stopped, hiccupping, with their voices wheezing, given up on by the healer, unable to make use of any kind of medicine, food, soup, or nourishment, lying on their final beds, about to go to other lives, sinking into the beginningless cyclic continuum of birth, old age, disease and death,}
with only a little life left, frightened by the fear of Yama’s men, under the power of the night of death,[xxx] breathing their last breaths in and out,[xxxi]
{with their teeth clenched, saying entreatingly “I have given gifts!”, entering the next life from the life in which they have acted,}
solitary, alone, and friendless, leaving this world and going to the next,[xxxii] walking on the great path, entering the great dreary forest, falling down into the great abyss, entering the great darkness, being washed away by the great ocean, driven by the winds of karma, going to a region where there are no signposts[xxxiii][xxxiv]
{entering the great battlefield, searching in space, surrounded by parents, brothers, sisters, sons, and daughters, with their breath stopping, saying ‘Share out my wealth!,’ saying ‘Oh no, mother! Oh no, father! Oh no, son!’, with their voices dying out, when only generosity, undergoing hardship in practice, and generosity are helpful …}
—for them, there is no refuge, no protection,[xxxv] no friend to help,[xxxvi] other than Dharma.

As for those who are beaten, tormented by fetters,
And located in various disastrous situations,
With many troubles and a thousand kinds of stress,
Facing various dangers and harsh sorrows,[lxvi]
May they all be set free from their fetters;
May those being beaten be set free from beatings;
May those condemned to die survive;
May those faced with disaster all be safe.

Conditioning has ignorance as its condition;
That conditioning itself also doesn’t really exist.
Conditioning and ignorance are empty;
They are naturally motionless.

Consciousness ceases and is born again;
The wise see with insight its arising and cessation.
It doesn’t come from anywhere and doesn’t go anywhere;
[240] Spiritual practitioners see it as empty, like an illusion.

Names are created by social convention;
Names are seen, nominally;
One man is named Ratnacitra,
And another, Ratnottama.

He will never be born in the lower realms;
He is always handsome, bearing the major marks;
He always cultivates the five superknowledges;
That hero will stand in front of the Well-Gone Ones.

{When someone strikes a kettle-drum,
The sound doesn’t go to the directions—it has no arising;
In the same way, it does not cease in the directions.
Best of men, you see all things in this way.}

As the same text says,
The higher intention[xxxv] {of the Victors} is in order to cross over in an extraordinary manner.
Also, higher intention is explained as:
[286] Gentleness towards beings;[xxxvi]
friendliness towards sentient beings;
thinking of the well-being of the Noble Ones;
compassion towards the ignoble;
respect for spiritual teachers;
respect for spiritual teachers who are saved;
salvation for those not saved;[xxxvii]
a refuge for those who have no refuge;
an island for those who have no island;
rescue for those with no one to rescue them;
companionship for those who have no companion;
straightness for the crooked; clarity for the unruly;
honesty for the dishonest;
freedom from illusion for those deceived by illusions;[xxxviii]
gratitude for the ungrateful;
gratefulness for the vengeful;
help for those who have no one to help;
truthfulness for those living a lie;
humility for the arrogant;
not blaming those who have acted well;
not shining a light on the mistakes of others;
being on guard for those who do wrong;
not seeing any faults in those who practice skillful means;
being ready to listen to all those who are worthy of honor;
great respect for teachers …
And so on.

They don’t arouse malice towards others;
They are always calm and free from heedlessness.
Fire does not harm them, nor poison, nor weapons;
[303] They are objects of admiration to the multitude.

Those who place a single oil-lamp at a stūpa of a Buddha
Are taken from the lowest place up to the summit of existence;
Through this, their Buddha field is of the finest gold;
Their lifespan and glory are inexhaustible.

Those who offer songs at stūpas of the Blessed One
Will be aware, with pure eyes;
High-minded, their ears will be pure;
Their sense of smell is acute to the highest degree.

Your hair is soft, elegant, unctuous, and beautiful;
Your crown protuberance is like the king of mountains.
No crown protuberance is seen equal to yours;
Sage, the curl of hair between your eyebrows shines brilliantly.

Sage, you are pure in thought, word, and deed;
Unsmeared by the threefold world, like a lotus in the water.
You have a voice like Brahmā and a song like the sparrow;
I revere you, who have gone beyond the threefold world.

Some by the door of offerings to the Tathāgatas;
By the door of generosity and inconceivable renunciation;
By the door of abilities and moral discipline, leaving everything behind;
By the door of the unshakeability of indestructible patient endurance;

Some by the door of vows to persevere in austerity;
By the door of resting in tranquil meditative stability;
By the door of wisdom that investigates for one’s own benefit;
By the door of all the thousands of skillful means;

By the door of the divine abidings and the superknowledges;
By the door of seeking to help others and the ways of bringing people together;
By the door of gathering goodness and pristine awareness;
By the door of the liberation that depends on truth;

Some by the door of the powers, the faculties, and the path;
By the door of liberation by means of the Way of the Disciples;
By the door of the purity of the Way of Conditions;[7]
By the door of the miracles of the highest Way;

Some by the door of impermanence and suffering;
Some by the door of no self and no life force;
By the door of conceptions of foulness and freedom from desire;[xxxi]
By the door of peaceful meditative absorption and cessation.

Among some, they teach using Dravidian words;
They teach the truth using very secret words;
Among some, with clear and straightforward words;
Among some, with secret divine words;

Among some, with words divided into syllables;
With adamantine words that investigate meanings;
With words of knowledge that subdue debate opponents;
With words that set people free from treatises that are contrary to Dharma;

Among some, with words from human languages;
With words that engage with all aspects of etymology:
Among some, with words of divine etymology;
With words whose etymology derives from the serpent-spirits or the tree-spirits;

When someone has died and gone into the womb,
A distinct child is born;
When the child has ceased, there is adolescence;
The young adult comes to destroy that.
